# Expo + React Native Client

## Stack

- **Expo** for build tooling, OTA updates, and native module access.
- **React Native Web** for the browser target; share 95%+ of UI between platforms.
- **Rich text:** Lexical or TipTap with custom `@mention` nodes synced to Markdown.

Pick one editor and use it consistently. Do not mix both in the same app.

## Layout

```
frontend/
├── app/              # Expo Router screens (or src/screens/)
├── src/
│   ├── api/          # HTTP client — all backend calls
│   ├── components/
│   ├── editor/       # Lexical/TipTap config, mention nodes
│   ├── hooks/
│   └── platform/     # Storage, notifications, device — no direct RN APIs in screens
├── app.json
└── package.json
```

## API access

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — fetch in a screen component
const res = await fetch(`${url}/notes`);

// ✅ GOOD — use the api client layer
import { listNotes } from '@/api/notes';
const notes = await listNotes();
```

Backend URLs come from config (`process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL`), never hardcoded in components.

## Platform APIs

Storage, notifications, and device info go through `src/platform/` — not `AsyncStorage`, `expo-notifications`, or `Platform` directly from screens.

## Rich-text editor

- Custom inline nodes for `@person` mentions with type-ahead search overlays.
- Serialize editor state to Markdown for API payloads and session snapshots.
- Editor changes stay local until the user completes a session; AI never silently mutates note text.

## Async UI

Every async operation needs loading and error states. Use platform-appropriate feedback (ActivityIndicator, toast).

## Styling

Prefer React Native `StyleSheet` or a cross-platform library (e.g. NativeWind). Avoid web-only CSS in shared components.

Adjust path globs if the client directory differs (e.g. `mobile/**/*.{ts,tsx}`).
